{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <b>8 sec\/speed 7<b>. Melt chocolate <b>4 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and melt <b>1 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and use melted chocolate to line inside of ice cream cones. Once the internal cone is covered with a thin layer of chocolate, turn upside down on a cooling rack and allow to drain. Refrigerate to set chocolate. Clean mixing bowl.","Place strawberries and sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add gelatin and heat <b>5 min\/140°F\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place cream cheese and whipping cream into mixing bowl and mix <b>45 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add reserved strawberry mixture and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate 45-60 minutes.","Transfer strawberry mousse into an icing bag with a star tip. Place 1 marshmallow into the base of each cone, pipe chilled strawberry mousse into cones and garnish with fresh mint leaves. Refrigerate until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 ½ oz dark chocolate, to line ice cream cones","10 waffle cones (see Tip)","10 ½ oz fresh strawberries, hulled and cut in half","7 oz sugar","2 tsp unflavored gelatin powder","6 ½ oz cream cheese","9 oz heavy whipping cream","10 marshmallows","fresh mint leaves, to garnish"]}],"id":"r109372","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-cVE4Fs5d15s\/XZWeNxJePfI\/AAAAAAAAeww\/8noGNom5yuQEBECIeA5jFAt0VoZvUO_4ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_VOg4rIrvvrEdCK2T.png","title":"Strawberry Mousse Waffle Cones","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34 g","calories":"690 kJ \/ 165 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cooling rack, icing bag and (star) piping tip, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Garnish the strawberry mousse with candy sprinkles or melted chocolate.","Use an ice cream cone stand or place each cone in a tall glass for support while filling and as a place to hold until serving.","If using a flat based cone, you will need 10 extra marshmallows to fill the space in the base of the cone.","Store bought chocolate-lined waffle cones will save time.","Try other fresh fruits like blackberries, raspberries or mangos.","For a firmer, richer mousse, replace organic heavy whipping cream with double cream."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h","10 pieces"]}